The LaTeX Project Public License (LPPL) is the primary license under which
the LaTeX kernel and the base LaTeX packages are distributed.

You may use this software and refer to it by its name if and only if you
fulfill the conditions of this license.

If you receive only part of this software, you may distribute it under the
terms of this license.

DEFINITIONS
===========

In this license document the following terms are used:

  "Work"         - any files distributed under the terms of this license.
  "Derived Work" - any work that under any applicable law is derived from
                   the Work.
  "Modification" - any procedure that produces a Derived Work under any
                   applicable law.
  "Distribute"   - making copies of the Work available from one person to
                   another, in whole or in part.
  "Compiled Work"- a version of the Work processed by a computer program
                   into some other form (e.g. a PDF file).
  "Current Maintainer" - a person or persons nominated as such within the
                   Work.
  "Base Interpreter" - a program or process that is normally needed for
                   running or interpreting a part of the Work.

CONDITIONS ON DISTRIBUTION AND MODIFICATION
============================================

1.  Activities other than distribution and/or modification of the Work are
    not covered by this license; they are outside its scope.

2.  You may, without restriction, reproduce the Work, translate it into
    another language, or use it for any purpose, provided that in doing so
    you do not Modify the Work.

3.  You may distribute a copy of the Work in its unmodified form, provided
    that you include a clear statement that the Work is distributed under
    the terms of this license and that this license applies to the Work, and
    provided further that:

    a. you include a copy of this license with the Work, or
    b. you provide the URI from which a copy of this license can be obtained.

4.  You may distribute a Compiled Work that has been generated from a
    complete, unmodified copy of the Work as distributed under Clause 3
    above, as long as that Compiled Work is distributed under the terms of
    this license.

5.  You may distribute a Derived Work from the Work under the conditions
    of Clause 4 above, provided that your Derived Work does not use the
    reserved name(s) of the Work, and provided furthermore that:

    a. You rename any non-standard file formats you use from those of the
       original Work so as to not be confused with the Work's file formats.
    b. You include a prominent statement in your Derived Work that it is a
       derivative of the Work, and that the original Work is distributed
       under the terms of this license.

6.  No restrictions are placed on installing and using this software.

7.  If the Work is labeled "unamaintained", then the Current Maintainer
    may be understood to be any person who distributes the Work.

